  "original_title": "\u201c\u0bb5\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bae\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bc8 \u0ba4\u0bc0\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0bb2\u201d - \u0b85\u0bae\u0bc6\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbe",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "\u201cViolence is not the solution\u201d - USA",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "\"Violence is not the solution,\" said Julie Sung, the American ambassador to Sri Lanka, and requested the protestors to \"please remain calm\".",
        "He also said, \"I remind you that the army and the police should give space to the peaceful protestors and provide security.\"",
        "Meanwhile, Julie Sung pointed out in her post that \"confusion and multiplicity will not bring economic or political stability to Sri Lankans at this stage.\"",
        "Violence is not an answer. If you are going to protest, please do so peacefully. And reminding military & police to grant peaceful protesters the space and security to do so. Chaos & force will not fix the economy or bring the political stability that Sri Lankans need right now."
      ],
